      • process

        public void process()
             throws Exception
        Description copied from class: NioPipeline
        Called when there are bytes available for reading, or space available to write. Any exception that leads to a termination of the connection like an IOException should not be handled in the handle method but should be propagated. The reason behind this is that the handle logic already is complicated enough and by pulling it out the flow will be easier to understand.
        Specified by:
        process in class NioPipeline
        Throws:
        Exception

      • requestMigration

        public void requestMigration(NioThread newOwner)
        Description copied from interface: MigratablePipeline
        Requests the MigratablePipeline to move to the new NioThread. This call will not wait for the migration to complete. This method can be called by any thread, and will probably be called by the IOBalancer. Call is ignored when pipeline is moving to the same NioThread.
        Specified by:
        requestMigration in interface MigratablePipeline
        Parameters:
        newOwner - the NioThread that is going to own this MigratablePipeline
